init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: America was the only nation left in isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I don't know sir...What did the Russians say?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The first advisor spoke up again, "Well sir...we have no standing.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "But we're an economic and military powerhouse!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You know, even in the days leading up to the return we had many who said that it was a mistake.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We are going to take a page from the Russians and continue to cultivate our ideals here in isolation.
